==Skill choice==
This section lists the experience rewards that can be allotted to a skill of the player's choosing, usually in the form of a lamp or book. It is recommended putting such experience rewards on skills that are slow or expensive to train, such as [[Slayer]], [[Runecraft]], [[Agility]], [[Construction]], or [[Herblore]].
<div class="qc-active">
{{SkillChoice|Any}}
</div>

==Other==
*[[Observatory Quest]] - 875 experience in [[Attack]], [[Strength]], [[Defence]], or [[Hitpoints]] is a possible reward from completing the quest, depending on the constellation players observe, which is random. Some constellations do not give experience in any skill but give items instead.
*The [[Varrock Museum]] - After completing a specific set of quests, players can speak to [[Historian Minas]] to inform him of their endeavours and their discoveries during these quests. Players will receive [[Kudos]] in addition to lamps which grant experience in a skill of the player's choosing. Players can receive additional experience from Kudos by speaking to the Varrock Museum's [[Information clerk]].
*[[Biohazard]] - After completing, players can access the [[Combat Training Camp]], which has unique combat dummies. 300 total [[Attack]] experience can can be gained by attacking the dummy for 50 experience per hit, up to a total of 6 hits.
*[[Shades of Mort'ton]] - During or after the quest, players can give the [[Diary (Shades of Mort'ton)|Diary]] obtained at the beginning of the quest to the [[Apothecary]] in [[Varrock]] for 335 [[Herblore]] experience. This can only be done once.
*[[While Guthix Sleeps]] - Gives [[Slayer]] experience equal to 15x the player's level after speaking with [[Kuradal]] about [[Duradel]].

== Quests that do not grant any experience rewards ==

This does not include any quests that reward tomes, lamps, or other ways to get experience after the quest has been completed, but where the quest itself does not have a direct experience reward.

